g.text: New issues are automatically set to NEW.
Once properly filled, author must set it to ready to PROCESS.
Then maintainers can either add it to the main BACKLOG.
Note that to be added to the BACKLOG, maintainers must compute priority using the scoring system.
At any time a BACKLOG issue can be picked to be implemented: ACTIVE.
Once confident enough with implementation and unit/integration tests, author should set it to TEST.
Any maintainer will have to thoroughly perform real world usage testing before updating the status to REVIEW.
Code REVIEW is again performed by a maintainer.
He can require CHANGES or validate and request a REBASE if needed, or directly merge the issue (DONE).
Note that at any point an issue can be CANCELLED.
